      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SONGAR OSCAR (1) promising type who notched his 7th career success when too good (17.16) at Taree Super Track last time. Has never missed the frame at the trip from five starts. Drawn the fence and expected to go close. LARNIE'S MAGIC (8) is a fast dog well performed over the sprint races. Kept coming to finish fourth over 388m at Gosford (22.52) latest in a Grade 3/4. Form at the trip strong including one wins. Safe beginner but wide box to overcome and will need some luck. Key runner who gets her chance to atone. YOUNG ENERGY (6) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by 0.8 lengths at this track in a handy 15.92 beating DIVA'S DELIGHT. The form out of her last race has been franked. Can measure up again. RAINING BOURBON (2) is worth consideration after filling a hole at this course and distance last start.",
